window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A killer is playing cat and mouse...and winning. </b></p> <p>DCI Whitney Walker’s in trouble. She’s threatened with demotion if she screws up another case. So, when a killer starts murdering female students, it’s a chance to redeem herself.&nbsp;</p> <p>Forensic psychologist, Dr. Georgina Cavendish, has spent her life inside the university walls, but when one of her students is murdered, she steps out from behind the text books and puts her skills to the test.&nbsp;</p> <p>The two headstrong women join forces to stop the killer. But sparks fly when real world policing meets academic theory, and it’s not a pretty sight.&nbsp;</p> <p><i>Deadly Games</i> is the first book in the Cavendish &amp; Walker crime fiction series. If you like serial killer mysteries and psychological intrigue, then you’ll love Sally Rigby’s thrilling listen performed by award-winning narrator Clare Corbett.&nbsp;</p> <p><i>Includes a special bonus note from the author.</i></p>"; 
